text: Capes track off to a flying start 0:00 AM EMMA HOPE NEARLY 200 people signed up to walk the new Three Capes Track within the first five hours of bookings opening. Qantas pilots in the pink 21:39 PM Robyn Ironside National Aviation Writer THE Flying Kangaroo will remain a glorious red but next month Qantas pilots will get into the pink for a worthy cause. Drugs, murder and stalkers: ‘It was unimaginable’ 18:45 PM JENNY HEWETT THERE’S no shortage of star-spotting tours in Hollywood, but when this Australian traveller joined a tour overseas, she ended up plunged into a world of death, despair and tragedy. Sex-fuelled festival with no rules 17:05 PM ISABEL THOMSON-OFFICER THE most debaucherous festival on Earth involves rampant drugs and sex. But there’s more to it than you think. WARNING: Nudity. High-speed train to reach speeds of 1200km/h 15:29 PM Rowena Ryan FASTER than a plane, billionaire Elon Musk has unveiled plans for a high-speed train between Madrid and Barcelona that would take just 30 minutes. There’s something strange about this airport 12:13 PM Scott Mayerowitz PASSENGERS flying in to this location may not realise it, but there’s something rather important that’s missing from what could be the world’s loneliest airport. Photos that are so Australian it hurts 12:09 PM KATE SCHNEIDER YES, that’s a crocodile in the back of a ute, but it has nothing on Vegemite flavoured chocolate. Welcome to Australia, the weirdest country on the planet.
